00:29:45.400 --> 00:29:47.363 align:middle line:84%
And then we start looking
for those planets.

00:29:47.363 --> 00:29:49.030 align:middle line:84%
And then when we
discover those planets,

00:29:49.030 --> 00:29:52.810 align:middle line:84%
we ask, well, do any of
those planets have water?

00:29:52.810 --> 00:29:56.110 align:middle line:84%
Oh, well, if they have
water, do they have life?

00:29:56.110 --> 00:29:59.380 align:middle line:84%
And then that ultimately
leads to further questions

00:29:59.380 --> 00:30:01.900 align:middle line:84%
and further observations
and further questions

00:30:01.900 --> 00:30:02.960 align:middle line:90%
and further testing.

00:30:02.960 --> 00:30:06.280 align:middle line:84%
So science is all
about a process that

00:30:06.280 --> 00:30:08.470 align:middle line:84%
starts with observing
and asking questions

00:30:08.470 --> 00:30:10.930 align:middle line:84%
and then goes on to
trying things out.

00:30:10.930 --> 00:30:14.860 align:middle line:10%
>> Asking a question, looking
around you to support whether

00:30:14.860 --> 00:30:19.250 align:middle line:10%
that question is valid or
invalid, gathering data,

00:30:19.250 --> 00:30:21.040 align:middle line:10%
analyzing that data.

00:30:21.040 --> 00:30:24.160 align:middle line:10%
We therefore hand
off all of that work

00:30:24.160 --> 00:30:26.620 align:middle line:10%
to a peer, someone
in our field who

00:30:26.620 --> 00:30:29.890 align:middle line:10%
knows as much or more than
we do, who can read it

00:30:29.890 --> 00:30:33.640 align:middle line:10%
and double-check that
the analysis of our data

00:30:33.640 --> 00:30:36.010 align:middle line:10%
was valid and
therefore validates

00:30:36.010 --> 00:30:39.580 align:middle line:10%
whether our conclusions
are appropriate or not.

00:30:39.580 --> 00:30:44.020 align:middle line:84%
The major differentiating
factor is peer review.

00:30:44.020 --> 00:30:45.760 align:middle line:90%
Don't just believe me.

00:30:45.760 --> 00:30:48.130 align:middle line:84%
I'm not the snake oil
salesman where you should just

00:30:48.130 --> 00:30:49.600 align:middle line:90%
take my word for it.

00:30:49.600 --> 00:30:52.690 align:middle line:84%
And that scientific
method, that peer review,

00:30:52.690 --> 00:30:55.930 align:middle line:84%
is what holds our
feet to the fire.

00:30:55.930 --> 00:30:59.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, because it gives
us a truer grasp of reality,

00:30:59.050 --> 00:31:00.990 align:middle line:90%
I think.

00:31:00.990 --> 00:31:04.618 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
important nowadays.

00:31:04.618 --> 00:31:06.910 align:middle line:10%
>> When I work with students,
